          "prednisone",
          "neck pain",
          "shoulder pain",
          "left finger injury",
          "neuropathy in one leg from knee to foot",
          "peripheral neuropathy"
        ]
      },
      {
        "heading": "Clinical Note",
        "section_value": "The patient is a veteran and receives 1% disability.\nCURRENT MEDICATIONS\nGabapentin tablet.\nPrednisone tablet.\nPHYSICAL EXAM\nConstitutional\nElderly Caucasian male in no apparent distress. Presents in wheelchair.\nNeurologic\nUpper extremities: 1+ bilateral biceps, triceps, brachioradialis, reflexes bilaterally, negative. Negative Hoffman's\nGait: Not assessed today.",
        "medical_concepts": [
          "gabapentin",
          "prednisone",
          "wheelchair use",
          "biceps reflex",
          "triceps reflex",
          "brachioradialis reflex",
          "Hoffman's sign",
          "gait assessment"
        ]
      },
      {
        "heading": "Clinical Note",
        "section_value": "Strength\nUpper extremities: Normal throughout the biceps, triceps, deltoid, grip strength, and finger abduction, bilaterally.\nSensation: Intact to light touch throughout the upper and lower extremities.\nMusculoskeletal\nCervical: Nontender over cervical spine. Mildly restricted cervical extension and right and left lateral rotation, which is symmetric, which gives him mild lateral neck pain, but no radicular pain. Spurling's maneuver is benign.\nRESULTS\nX-ray Cervical Spine, 06/04/2021.\nImpression: Significant disc degeneration at C5-6 and to a lesser extent C4-5 and C3-4. Significant lower facet arthropathy. C6-7 and C7-T1 are difficult to visualize in the current x-rays.\nASSESSMENT\n• Left upper extremity neuropathy, suspicious for cervical radiculopathy, possible contribution of peripheral neuropathy",
        "medical_concepts": [
          "biceps strength",
          "triceps strength",
          "deltoid strength",
          "grip strength",
          "finger abduction strength",
          "light touch sensation",
          "cervical spine tenderness",
