          "disc degeneration at C3-4",
          "facet arthropathy",
          "C6-7 visualization difficulty",
          "C7-T1 visualization difficulty",
          "left upper extremity neuropathy"
        ]
      },
      {
        "heading": "Clinical Note",
        "section_value": "• Neck pain in the setting of arthritis and disc generation\nPLAN\nI suspect that this is a flare of cervical radiculopathy. I am going to set him up for a cervical MRI. We will tentatively plan for a left C7-T1 epidural afterwards, although the exact level will be pending the MRI results. He will continue his home exercise program as well as twice daily gabapentin. We will follow up with him afterwards to determine his level of relief. He denies any blood thinners.\nThis plan was discussed in detail with the patient who is in agreement.\nINSTRUCTIONS\nContinue home exercise program and twice daily gabapentin. Schedule MRI and epidural injection. Follow-up after epidural.",
